This paper deals with analyzing the link structure of a domain-specific subset of Wikipedia articles related to art history. The paper uses an established domain-specific person name authority, the Getty Union List of Artist Names (ULAN), to identify relevant actors and examines the link structure between these resources. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), computers and society (cs.CY), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
